# API Controllers

## Route prefix

`@Controller('auth')` → `/v1/auth/*`. No global `/api` prefix.

## Nested routes (RouterModule)

Paths not visible from `@Controller()` alone:

| Full path | Module |
|---|---|
| `/v1/users/me/*` | `src/modules/user/me/` |
| `/v1/users/me/listings/*` | `src/modules/user/me/listing/` |
| `/v1/users/agents` | `src/modules/user/user.controller.ts` |
| `/v1/users/agents/:agentId/reviews` | `src/modules/user/review/` |
| `/v1/real-estate-developers` | developer catalog |
| `/v1/real-estate-developers/projects` | projects list |
| `/v1/real-estate-developers/projects/:projectId/properties` | properties |

See `docs/api-routes.md` for the full map.

## Public + optional auth

`@Public()` with `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)` allows unauthenticated access but attaches `user` when a valid Bearer token is present (used on listing browse endpoints).

## Auth throttling

Apply `@AuthThrottle()` / `@StrictAuthThrottle()` on register, login, and password-reset endpoints.
